data.title: Pastor David Robbins — Fellowship Community Church
data.text:
David Robbins

David Robbins serves as FCC’s Worship Pastor. He and his wife, Anna, have been married for five years and are blessed with four children. They have two dogs, named Baskin Robbins and Noir. Tim Keller and Bob Kauflin have been two of the most influential writers and speakers in David’s life and ministry. David’s motivation is the calling God has put on his life to lead others to knowing Him more intimately through worship. His passion is to see others devoting their lives and their gifts to the Lord, especially in the realm of music.

Education: Bachelor’s in Worship Leadership, with a concentration in Church Ministry from the University of Mobile and a M.A. in Christian Apologetics from the New Orleans Baptist Theological Seminary.
